com.navis.framework.persistence.hibernate

Class PersistenceTemplateInterceptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.navis.framework.persistence.hibernate.PersistenceTemplateInterceptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.aopalliance.aop.Advice, org.aopalliance.intercept.Interceptor, org.aopalliance.intercept.MethodInterceptor

    public final class PersistenceTemplateInterceptor
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.aopalliance.intercept.MethodInterceptor
    Adds session/transaction/message collector to a method via PersistenceTemplate. Supports two transaction propagation modes. Default behavior is REQUIRED transaction propagation mode- just piggy back on preexisting session if there are any Be extremely careful with REQUIRES_NEW as any previous sql statements to an existing sql statements to flush.
    See Also:
    PersistenceTemplate
